            <Label 
                Content="Map" 
                FontSize="30" 
                FontWeight="Bold"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 10"
                Text="When you open the map tab on the navigation bar, a page with a list of events on the left side and a map on the right side will appear."/>
            <Image Width="1200" Source="../../Resources/Images/MapView.png"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 20 0 20"
                Text="The map supports draging the events from the list onto the map and also dragging the events from the map back to the list. Note that dropping the event on the map will remove it from the list."/>
            <Image Width="1200" Source="../../Resources/Images/DragFromList.png" Margin="0 20 0 60"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="To start the drag and drop process of an event from the list, press the left click of your mouse and hold it. Then just simply drag it onto the map to the desired location."/>
            <Image Width="1200" Source="../../Resources/Images/DraggedToMap.png" Margin="0 20 0 60"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="You can also move the event around on the map by holding left click, after which a little rectangle will appear next to your mouse which indicates that the dragging process has started. NOTE THAT EVENTS CANNOT OVERLAP AND IF YOU WERE GOING TO PLACE AN EVENT OVER AN EXISTING ONE, IT WILL BE PUT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL PLACE."/>
            <Image Width="500" Source="../../Resources/Images/DraggedEventView.png" Margin="0 20 0 60"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Dragging an event from a map is also a seamless process, just hold the left click on the event and drag it onto the list, and it will be successfully listed."/>
            <Image Width="500" Source="../../Resources/Images/DragginTheEventBackToList.png" Margin="0 20 0 60"/>
            <Image Width="500" Source="../../Resources/Images/DragEventToList.png" Margin="0 20 0 60"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="You can also filter the events on the map by name, just start typing out the name of a desired event and the events you see will change."/>

            <Label 
                Content="Events" 
                FontSize="30" 
                FontWeight="Bold"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Locating to the 'EVENTS' page is done through clicking on the 'EVENTS' button in the navigation bar at the top part of the screen. There you will be met with search inputs, a filter input, a grid with all tags displayed and action buttons for adding, editing or showing details of a certain event."/>

            <Label 
                Content="Searching" 
                FontSize="20" 
                FontWeight="Bold"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Searcing is done by inputing values into search fields and pressing the 'Search' button which will show the search results in the grid. When putting in search inputs, keep in mind the data validations such as not inputing anything other than letters into text inputs etc. 'Label', 'Name', 'Description', 'Country', 'City' are all text fields and will allow only letters to be put in. 'Event type' and 'Attendance' fields are dropdown lists, where you choose from a list of options. 'Is charity' fields is a check box which you check and uncheck by clicking on it, there are 'Event date from' and 'Event date to' fields where you pick a date by clicking on the small calendar icon and selecting the desired date. Fields 'Expenses from' and 'Expenses to' expect a decimal number with 2 decimal points and a dot as a denominator."/>

            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="You can clear the search result by pressing the 'Clear search' button which will restore the original tag list and will empty out the search inputs."/>
            <Label 
                Content="Filtering" 
                FontSize="20" 
                FontWeight="Bold"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="To filter out grid events, just start typing in the filter field and results will change in real time. The events are filtered by label, name, description, attendance, city, country and average hosting expenses. Clearing out the filter will reset the results."/>
            <Label 
                Content="Adding an event" 
                FontSize="20" 
                FontWeight="Bold"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>

            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="To go to the page where you can add a new event, Press the green 'Add' button under the grid."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="On the add page you will be presented with fields where you can input a label, name, description, choose the type of the event and the attendance from a dropdown list, check is it a charity event, select an icon, type in the average hosting expenses, event date."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Label, Name, Description, Country and City are text inputs and they will allow you to input only letters. Event type and Attendance fields are dropdown lists which will allow you to choose from a list of options. Average hosting expenses is a field which will expect a decimal format with 2 decimals and a dot as a separator. There is also an Event date field which will let you pick out a date."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="There will also be a 'Select icon' button displayed. By clicking on it, a folder explorer will appear prompting you to choose an icon. Choose the icon and press save. The chosen icon will be displayed next to the button. If no Icon is selected, the event will have the icon of the chose event type for that event."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Also there will be a dropdown list of Tags. Choose a tag from the list and press on the blue + button next to the list. You will add a tag for this event and it will be displayed in the list below. You will not be able to add the same tag twice."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Next to the list that displays selected tags, there is a red cross button. It will be disabled unless you select a tag. Then you can press the button to remove the selected tag from the list."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="The same goes for Previous event dates. Select a date and press the blue + button to add it to the list of previous dates. You will not be able to add the same date twice."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Next to the list that displays selected previous event dates, there is a red cross button. It will be disabled unless you select a date. Then you can press the button to remove the selected date from the list."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="Adding tags or previous event dates is not required, nor is the adding of an icon."/>
            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="If the green 'Add' button is enabled, that means you put in valid values and can therefore proceed with adding the Event. By clicking this button, you will be taken back to the event grid and your newly added event will be displayed"/>

            <TextBlock 
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                FontSize="20"
                TextWrapping="Wrap" 
                Width="1000"
                Margin="0 0 0 50"
                Text="If you do not want to add a new event, you can click the red button 'Cancel' which will take you back to the grid and no changes will be made."/>
